R Packages on GitHub


accelerometry

  • Functions for processing accelerometer data.
  • C++ code used internally for speed.

dvmisc

  • Convenience functions, moving window statistics, and graphics.
  • E.g. run and summarize simulations, plot histogram with fitted densities and AICs.

nhanesaccel

  • Process accelerometer data from NHANES 2003-2006.
  • Highly customizable to accommodate various methods.
  • Roughly 90x faster than National Cancer Institutes SAS programs.

nhanesdata

  • Data from continuous NHANES (years 1999-2016).
  • Makes it easy to load data into R.

pooling

  • Fit poolwise regression models.
  • Maximum likelihood methods accounting for assay measurement errors.
  • Also has tools for designing pooling studies (e.g.optimal pool size, cost savings).

stocks

  • Stock market analysis.
  • Calculate metrics, visualize 2- and 3-fund portfolios, etc.

tab

  • Create summary tables for statistical reports.
  • Contingency tables, comparison of means/medians, GLMs, GEEs, Cox PH.
